# Product Requirements Document (PRD)
# AI Navigation

**Version:** 1.0
**Status:** Draft
**Owner:** Product Team

---

## 1. Vision

Traditional navigation apps give mechanical, robotic instructions — precise but impersonal ("In 300 meters, turn right onto Elm Street"). Humans don't navigate that way; they say things like *"Turn right just after the gas station"* or *"Stay on this road until you see the church, then take a left."*

**AI Navigation's vision** is to make digital navigation feel like getting directions from a knowledgeable friend in the car with you — natural, contextual, landmark-aware, and reassuring — while still using the accuracy and coverage of Google Maps under the hood.

> "Navigation that talks to you like a person, not a machine."

Long-term, AI Navigation aims to become the natural-language layer of choice for human-centered wayfinding — usable standalone or eventually licensed as an SDK/API layer for other mapping products.

---

## 2. Target Users

| Segment | Description | Needs |
|---|---|---|
| **Everyday commuters** | People driving/walking familiar or semi-familiar routes daily | Quick, low-cognitive-load guidance; reduce reliance on staring at screen |
| **Tourists & travelers** | Visiting unfamiliar cities, often on foot or rideshare | Clear, landmark-based directions; confidence in unfamiliar areas |
| **New drivers / anxious navigators** | Users who find rapid distance-based instructions stressful | Calm, reassuring, conversational tone; more lead-time on cues |
| **Ride-share & delivery drivers** | Frequent, varied trips across a city | Fast, unambiguous guidance that reduces missed turns and wrong stops |
| **Accessibility-focused users** | Visually impaired or low-vision users relying heavily on audio guidance | Rich, descriptive audio cues beyond simple distance countdowns |

### Primary persona (MVP focus)
**"Priya, 29, urban commuter"** — Drives a mix of familiar and new routes, currently uses Google Maps/Waze, gets mildly annoyed by robotic phrasing and wants something that feels more natural, especially in complex intersections.

