## 3. Competitors

| Competitor | Strength | Gap AI Navigation Targets |
|---|---|---|
| **Google Maps** | Best-in-class map data, routing accuracy, global coverage | Instructions are literal/mechanical, not conversational or landmark-rich by default |
| **Waze** | Strong community-driven real-time data (traffic, hazards, police) | Focused on speed/traffic alerts, not natural language quality |
| **Apple Maps** | Clean UX, tight OS integration | Similar mechanical instruction style; limited landmark usage |
| **HERE WeGo** | Offline maps, enterprise/logistics use | Not consumer-friendly, lacks conversational tone |
| **Voice assistants (Siri/Google Assistant nav mode)** | Voice-first interaction | Not purpose-built for continuous, context-aware navigation narration |

**Differentiation:** AI Navigation doesn't try to out-map Google Maps — it uses Google Maps as the routing/data backbone and differentiates entirely on the **natural-language, human-like guidance layer** and conversational UX on top of it.

