## 5. MVP (Minimum Viable Product)

**Goal:** Prove that AI-generated, human-like navigation instructions are viable, accurate, and preferred over standard robotic instructions — for a single core use case (driving).

### MVP Scope
- ✅ Flutter app (iOS + Android) with Google Maps SDK map view
- ✅ Origin → destination route search (Google Maps Directions API)
- ✅ Backend (FastAPI) service that converts raw Google Maps steps into human-like, landmark-referenced instructions
- ✅ Text-to-speech narration of instructions
- ✅ Basic Firebase authentication (email + Google sign-in)
- ✅ Trip start/end logging to PostgreSQL
- ✅ Single navigation mode: **driving only**
- ✅ Basic error handling (no route found, GPS loss, API failure fallback to standard instructions)

### Explicitly Out of Scope for MVP
- ❌ Walking/cycling/transit modes
- ❌ Real-time rerouting on traffic changes
- ❌ Personalization/learning user style
- ❌ Offline maps/caching
- ❌ Social/community features (hazard reporting, etc.)

